==English==

===Etymology===
Invented by ''[[Polish#Adjective|Polish]]'' [[logician]] Jan Łukasiewicz.

===Noun===
'''[[Polish#Adjective|Polish]] [[notation]]'''

# {{mathematics}} an [[arithmetic]] [[formula]] notation in which [[operation]]s precede their [[operand]]s; thus 3 * (4 + 7) is written as * 3 + 4 7
# {{logic}} a [[logical]] [[formula]] notation in which [[quantifier]]s and [[operator]]s precede their [[operand]]s; thus [[infix notation]] ''A'' '''[[AND]]''' ''B'' is written as '''AND''' ''A'' ''B''.

